=== DECISIONS.md ===
# Decisions Register

<!-- Append-only. Never edit or remove existing rows.
     To reverse a decision, add a new row that supersedes it.
     Read this file at the start of any planning or research phase. -->

| # | When | Scope | Decision | Choice | Rationale | Revisable? | Made By |
|---|------|-------|----------|--------|-----------|------------|---------|
| D001 |  | architecture | Tech stack cho hệ thống quản lý quán trà sữa | Next.js 14+ (App Router) + Tailwind CSS + SQLite (Prisma) + SSE | Next.js cho full-stack trong một project. SQLite không cần cài DB server riêng — phù hợp chạy local. Tailwind cho UI nhanh. SSE cho real-time đơn giản không cần WebSocket server. | Yes | collaborative |
| D002 |  | architecture | Cơ chế QR ordering | QR tĩnh chứa URL http://<local-ip>:3000/order?table=N, in sẵn 10-20 mã dán tại bàn | QR tĩnh đơn giản, in một lần dùng mãi. Không cần dynamic QR hay session — table number là identity đủ cho quán tầm trung. | Yes | collaborative |
| D003 |  | architecture | Ai có quyền huỷ/sửa đơn hàng | Chỉ nhân viên được huỷ/sửa đơn từ dashboard. Khách không có nút huỷ/sửa trên trang order — cần báo nhân viên. | Tránh khách tự huỷ đơn gây mất kiểm soát. Quán tầm trung nhân viên gần bàn, báo trực tiếp nhanh hơn. Giữ UI khách đơn giản, logic phức tạp dồn về phía staff. | Yes | collaborative |
| D004 | M001/S03 | library | PDF generation library for QR code printables | pdfkit + qrcode npm packages — server-side PDF generation in Next.js Route Handler | PDFKit is pure Node.js with streaming API, supports A4 sizing and PNG image embedding from Buffer natively. Combined with qrcode's toBuffer() for PNG generation, gives a clean server-side pipeline with no browser dependencies. Alternatives rejected: jspdf (browser-first), @react-pdf/renderer (heavyweight overkill). Both qrcode and pdfkit are offline-compatible (R006). | Yes | agent |
| D005 | M001/S03 | architecture | Admin auth mechanism for /admin routes | Simple ADMIN_PASSWORD env var + httpOnly cookie. Next.js middleware on Edge runtime protects /admin/* except /admin/login. No hashing — plain comparison. Cookie set with sameSite:lax, no secure flag (HTTP local network). | Tea shop on local network doesn't need complex auth. Single password from env var is appropriate for admin access on internal WiFi. httpOnly cookie prevents JS theft. No rate limiting needed since attack surface is local network only. Edge-compatible middleware avoids Node.js runtime requirements. | Yes | agent |
| D006 | M002 planning | architecture | M002 slice decomposition: two vertical slices instead of three | S01: Menu Browsing (read path — QR to tabbed menu display), S02: Cart + Order Submission (write path — cart state, UI, API, confirmation). Rejected: three-slice split with standalone API slice. | A standalone API-only slice is a horizontal layer, not a vertical slice — it would only be verifiable via curl, not by a real user through the real interface. The order creation API belongs with the cart submission because they form a single demoable capability. Two slices maps to the natural boundary: the read path (S01 is independently valuable — QR codes lead to a real menu) and the write path (S02 completes the ordering flow end-to-end). | Yes | agent |
| D007 | M002 planning | architecture | Order creation uses Route Handler (POST /api/order) instead of Server Action | Route Handler at /api/order — JSON request/response pattern with explicit status codes and validation | Cart submission is a JSON payload from client-side state (not a form submission). Route Handler gives clean control over validation, error responses with specific status codes (400/404/409), and structured error payloads for unavailable items. Server Actions are form-oriented and would require workarounds for JSON payloads and custom error shapes. | Yes | agent |
| D008 | M003 planning | architecture | M003 slice decomposition: station-first vertical slices | S01: Bar Station End-to-End (SSE + API + UI proving the risky technology), S02: Kitchen + Overview + Cancel (extending proven patterns), S03: Notifications + Auto-Hide (additive polish). Three slices ordered by risk. | SSE is the only novel technology — building the bar station end-to-end proves it works through a real user-facing feature (not a spike). Kitchen and overview reuse the proven StationView and SSE infrastructure with minimal risk. Notifications are purely additive and can be descoped. This mirrors D006 reasoning (vertical slices over horizontal layers) but applied to the station topology. | Yes | agent |
| D009 | M003 planning | architecture | SSE subscriber registry with station-level filtering | Single SSE endpoint at /api/staff/orders/stream with ?station= query param. Subscriber registry on globalThis stores controller + station metadata. Broadcasts filter by station so bar clients only receive DRINK-relevant events. | Station-level SSE filtering reduces noise per client — bar doesn't need kitchen events. A single endpoint with query param is simpler than three separate SSE endpoints. The globalThis caching pattern is already proven by the Prisma singleton in this codebase. Filtering at broadcast time (not at subscription time) keeps the registry simple while still avoiding unnecessary event delivery. | Yes | agent |
| D010 | M003 planning | architecture | Shared StationView component parameterized by station type | Single StationView component accepting station prop ('bar'\|'kitchen'\|'all'). Each station page is a thin Server Component wrapper. Station determines: SSE filter, Vietnamese label ('Quầy Bar'/'Bếp'/'Tổng quan'), and which status transitions are available (station pages: PENDING→PREPARING→READY; overview: READY→SERVED). | All three stations share the same data shape (orders with items), same real-time mechanism (SSE), and same card layout. The only differences are filtering and available transitions. A parameterized component avoids triplicate code and ensures changes propagate consistently. This is the brownfield-bias choice — it extends the existing pattern of reusable components seen in M002's CartProvider/MenuView. | Yes | agent |


